POLOKWANE – Get your dancing shoes and vintage clothes ready for the Kofifi Dance Party Winter Edition themed Tot Piet Kom, Dobol tot Piet Kom. Kofifi Dance Party lovers can now start to prepare their vintage attire and accessories for the much-loved event in the City of Stars. Meropa Casino and Entertainment World is exited for June 25 when Mahlasedi Media Communication will host this popular annual event. Kofifi Dance Party Winter Edition will feature the music from various DJs, who promises to keep all the festival-goers on their feet. According to Mahlasedi Media Communication founder Fortune ‘DJ Cappuccino’ Maswanganyi, this is a one-of-a-kind event in Polokwane. “We are back again and happy to give guests an opportunity to dress up. “Even though we are still in lockdown level 1 of the pandemic, we will continue with the festival because most of the party-goers have already booked accommodation. “This is exactly the type of legacy project we need in the province; a very unique one that is going to last for many years. I am also happy people are attracted to the theme,” said Maswanganyi. Tickets are available at Computicket at R200 or send a WhatsApp to 063 284 2082 for the banking details. Tickets are limited and Covid-19 regulations will apply. Gates open at 18:00. 